This paper involves the use of deep learning algorithms to classify glaucomatous damage on fundus photographs, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of a convolutional neural network (CNN) for training the algorithm, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of spectral-domain optical coherence tomography (SDOCT) data, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of medical imaging, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
